  "body": "[comment]: # (Please replace ... with your information. Remove < and >)\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a developer or product manager, I want to change app configuration  without releasing app upgrade so that i can enable/disable/change features on the fly.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nApp configuration settings https://github.com/status-im/status-react/blob/develop/.env.prod should be adjustable on the fly without an app upgrade by using remote config.\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\n\r\nSince we already using Firebase for Push Notification, possible solution would be using Firebase Remote Config https://firebase.google.com/docs/remote-config/?authuser=0 \r\n\r\nObvious downside of this solution is becoming more dependent on Firebase services. Also, potential security issues may arise. Better alternatives are welcomed.\r\n\n\n<blockquote><img src=\"https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/11767950?s=400&v=4\" width=\"48\" align=\"right\"><div><img src=\"https://assets-cdn.github.com/favicon.ico\" height=\"14\"> GitHub</div><div><strong><a href=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-react\">status-im/status-react</a></strong></div><div>status-react - a free (libre) open source, mobile OS for Ethereum</div></blockquote>\n<blockquote><img src=\"https://firebase.google.com/_static/bdb9b43e5e/images/firebase/favicon.png?authuser=0\" width=\"48\" align=\"right\"><div>Firebase</div><div><strong><a href=\"https://firebase.google.com/docs/remote-config/\">Firebase Remote Config  |  Firebase</a></strong></div><div>Change the behavior and appearance of your app without publishing an app update, at no cost, for unlimited daily active users.</div></blockquote>",
